# Legacy locale redirects — English moved from /en/* to the apex when
# English became the default locale. 301 any old /en/* URL (stale index
# entries, external backlinks) to its unprefixed equivalent so they keep
# their link equity instead of 404ing.
#
# `:splat` is the part matched by `*`, so /en/pricing/ → /pricing/ and
# /en/ → / (empty splat). The bare /en (no trailing slash) needs its own
# rule since /en/* only matches paths under /en/.
/en/*  /:splat  301
/en    /        301
